May 6, 1991: The young police officer Alexander Falco has a bright future ahead of him, a wife and a little girl. 
Life decides otherwise: he takes a bullet in the head and goes into a coma. 
22 years later: Falco opens his eyes to a world he doesn't recognize. His wife has rebuilt her life, her daughter is an adult. 
And his former teammate, now Commissioner, offers him retirement. 
But Falco will not give up. Nonconformist, hothead, with an outstanding cop instinct, he returns to police investigation with the young and procedural Lieutenant Chevalier. 
In parallel, Falco will do anything to get his life back. 
After what he went through, nothing and nobody can stop him.
